First, figure out the maximal amount of torque you’ll need in ordinary operation - call this \tau_{max} .  Then, calculate the current limit I_{max} as follows:

I_{max} = I_{stall} * \frac{\tau_{max}}{\tau_{stall}}

where I_{stall} is the stall current of the motor and \tau_{stall} is the stall torque of the motor (you’ll have to account for gearing, ofc).
